The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Ondo has condemned the kidnapping and subsequent murder of the party’s chairman in Nasarawa State, Philip Shekwo. Ondo APC Chairmam, Engr. Ade Adetimehin, in a statement said the killing was unforgivable wickedness. Adetimehin, who urged security agencies to unmask the murderers, said the ease with which gunmen carry out their nefarious activities called for concerted efforts to ensure a more secured society for all Nigerians Adetimehin regretted that the Forum of APC State chairmen has been permanently denied Shekwo’ kindness, experience in party politics, and intelligent contributions during party meetings.